AnyEvent-DBD-mysql-Cluster

This module implements asyncronous interaction with a cluster of arbitrary 
number of master and replica mysql servers.

The goal is to maintain permannet connections to every server in a cluster
and provide convient interface to peek single server for every request,
spreading the load and beeing fault tolerant.

The main working horse under the hood is AnyEvent-DBD-mysql module
by Mons Anderson (mons@cpan.org) found at https://github.com/Mons/AnyEvent-DBD-mysql

The idea for this module was inspired by AnyEvent::Tarantool::Cluster module, 
found at https://github.com/Mons/AnyEvent-Tarantool/blob/master/lib/AnyEvent/Tarantool/Cluster.pm
and also created by Mons.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc AnyEvent::DBD::mysql::Cluster


